Implement every function listed in `ObjectiveTree/00.5-support-full-ncursesw-API/03-verify-window-api-coverage/missing-functions.md` as `terminal::Window` API and `Window::Impl` wrappers, keeping ncurses types hidden behind `Impl` and grouping new declarations in `Window.h` by the same invisible-island.net man page URL headings from that file.

In `Window.h`, add public declarations using the existing naming and overload style: strip ncurses-only `w`, `mv`, and `n` affixes where C++ overloading makes the signature distinct, keep the supported ncurses function name in the trailing declaration comment, and replace coordinate pairs with `Position` and size pairs with `Dimension`. Use `const` member functions for read-only queries. Unlike the earlier implementation objective, query functions whose return value is the requested property should return that value publicly: boolean property functions return `bool`, position queries return `Position`, dimension queries return `Dimension`, delay/region queries return an appropriate public value type, and conversion/query functions such as mouse coordinate transforms return a meaningful success/property value when that is what ncurses reports rather than an error status. Still avoid exposing `WINDOW*` or other ncurses-specific types in the public API.

Add one short single-line comment above each declaration when behavior, parameters, coordinate space, ownership, or side effects are not obvious. Public functions that only signal ncurses success/failure should not expose raw `int` status; assert or throw on failure as in the existing `Window` wrapper style.

In `Window.cxx`, each newly added public `Window` member should forward to the same-named `impl_` function with equivalent parameters, adapting only to public return-value policy. `Window::Impl` functions translate `Position` and `Dimension` to ncurses integers, call the exact ncursesw function named in the `Window.h` trailing comment, and return the underlying result or converted public value. Each `Impl` function must include a comment containing the relevant invisible-island.net man page URL, a blank `//` line, and a short excerpt/paraphrase from that man page explaining what the function does.
